<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName LSID="8624C0BF-7DAC-5E5D-9E1F-4F266473DD1C" authority="Speg., Anal. Mus. nac. B. Aires, Ser. 3 12: 401 (1909)" authorityName="Speg., Anal. Mus. nac. B. Aires, Ser. 3 12: 401" authorityYear="1909" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" genus="Ophiosphaerella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ophiosphaerella" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Ophiosphaerella Speg., Anal. Mus. nac. B. Aires, Ser. 3 12: 401 (1909)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Speg., Anal. Mus. nac. B. Aires, Ser. 3 12: 401" authorityYear="1909" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" genus="Ophiosphaerella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ophiosphaerella" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Ophiosphaerella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Spegazzini, C" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" refId="B55" refString="Spegazzini, C, 1909. Mycetes Argentinenses. Series IV. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural Buenos Aires. Ser. 3, 12: 257-458." title="Mycetes Argentinenses. Series IV. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural Buenos Aires. Ser. 3, 12: 257 - 458." year="1909">Spegazzini (1909)</bibRefCitation>
to accommodate 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. graminicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="graminicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">O. graminicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Speg. as the type species. The species of this genus are characterized by papillate ascomata bearing fissitunicate, cylindrical asci frequently narrower near the base, with a short furcate pedicel and filamentous, pale brown, multi-septate ascospores without swollen cells or separating into part spores. 
<bibRefCitation author="Barr, ME" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="501 - 505" refId="B6" refString="Barr, ME, 1987. New taxa and combinations in the Loculoascomycetes. Mycotaxon 29: 501 - 505" title="New taxa and combinations in the Loculoascomycetes." volume="29" year="1987">Barr (1987)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Speg., Anal. Mus. nac. B. Aires, Ser. 3 12: 401" authorityYear="1909" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" genus="Ophiosphaerella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ophiosphaerella" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Ophiosphaerella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Speg., Anal. Mus. nac. B. Aires, Ser. 3 12: 401" authorityYear="1909" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" genus="Ophiosphaerella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Phaeosphaeriaceae</taxonomicName>
and this was confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3114/sim.2009.64.04" author="Zhang, Y" journalOrPublisher="Studies in Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="85 - 102" refId="B73" refString="Zhang, Y, Schoch, CL, Fournier, J, Crous, PW, De Gruyter, J, Woudenberg, JHC, Hirayama, K, Tanaka, K, Pointing, SB, Spatafora, JW, Hyde, KD, 2009. Multi-locus phylogeny of Pleosporales: a taxonomic, ecological and evolutionary re-evaluation. Studies in Mycology 64: 85 - 102, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3114/sim.2009.64.04" title="Multi-locus phylogeny of Pleosporales: a taxonomic, ecological and evolutionary re-evaluation." url="https://doi.org/10.3114/sim.2009.64.04" volume="64" year="2009">Zhang et al. (2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-011-0117-x" author="Zhang, Y" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="1 - 225" refId="B74" refString="Zhang, Y, Crous, PW, Schoch, CL, Hyde, KD, 2012. Pleosporales. Fungal Diversity 52: 1 - 225, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-011-0117-x" title="Pleosporales." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-011-0117-x" volume="52" year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-013-0263-4" author="Hyde, KD" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="1 - 313" refId="B22" refString="Hyde, KD, Jones, EBG, Liu, JK, Ariyawansa, H, Boehm, E, Boonmee, S, Braun, U, Chomnunti, P, Crous, PW, Dai, DQ, Diederich, P, Dissanayake, A, Doilom, M, Doveri, F, Hongsanan, S, Jayawardena, R, Lawrey, JD, Li, YM, Liu, YX, Luecking, R, Monka, J, Muggia, L, Nelsen, MP, Pang, KL, Phookamsak, R, Senanayake, IC, Shearer, CA, Suetrong, S, Tanaka, K, Thambugala, KM, Wijayawardene, NN, Wikee, S, Wu, HX, Zhang, Y, Begona, AH, Alias, SA, Aptroot, A, Bahkali, AH, Bezerra, JL, Bhat, DJ, Camporesi, E, Chukea, E, Gueidan, C, Hawksworth, DL, Hirayama, K, Hoog, SD, Kang, JK, Knudsen, K, Li, WJ, Li, XH, Liu, ZY, Mapook, A, Mckenzie, EHC, Miller, AN, Mortimer, PE, Phillips, AJL, Raja, HA, Scheuer, C, Schumm, F, Taylor, JE, Tian, Q, Tibpromma, S, Wanasinghe, DN, Wang, Y, Xu, JC, Yacharoen, S, Yan, JY, Zang, M, 2013. Families of Dothideomycetes. Fungal Diversity 63: 1 - 313, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-013-0263-4" title="Families of Dothideomycetes." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-013-0263-4" volume="63" year="2013">Hyde et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
based on molecular phylogeny. Most 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Speg., Anal. Mus. nac. B. Aires, Ser. 3 12: 401" authorityYear="1909" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" genus="Ophiosphaerella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ophiosphaerella" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Ophiosphaerella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are often found as pathogens or saprobes worldwide on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Speg., Anal. Mus. nac. B. Aires, Ser. 3 12: 401" authorityYear="1909" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Poaceae" genus="Ophiosphaerella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Speg., Anal. Mus. nac. B. Aires, Ser. 3 12: 401" authorityYear="1909" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Ophiosphaerella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Cyperaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2000.12061162" author="Camara, MP" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="317 - 325" refId="B10" refString="Camara, MP, O'Neill, NR, Berkum, PV, Dernoeden, PH, Palm, ME, 2000. Ophiosphaerella agrostis sp. nov. and its relationship to other species of Ophiosphaerella. Mycologia 92: 317 - 325, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2000.12061162" title="Ophiosphaerella agrostis sp. nov. and its relationship to other species of Ophiosphaerella." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2000.12061162" volume="92" year="2000">
<normalizedToken originalValue="CÃ¢mara">Camara</normalizedToken>
et al. 2000
</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, twelve 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Speg., Anal. Mus. nac. B. Aires, Ser. 3 12: 401" authorityYear="1909" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" genus="Ophiosphaerella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ophiosphaerella" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Ophiosphaerella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are listed in 
<bibRefCitation author="Index Fungorum" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" publicationUrl="http://www.indexfungorum.org/names/Names.asp" refId="B25" refString="Index Fungorum, 2020. Index Fungorum. http://www.indexfungorum.org/names/Names.asp" title="Index Fungorum." url="http://www.indexfungorum.org/names/Names.asp" year="2020">Index Fungorum (2020)</bibRefCitation>
. In this study, we introduce 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tennakoon, C. H. Kuo &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2020" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" genus="Ophiosphaerella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ophiosphaerella taiwanensis" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="taiwanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Ophiosphaerella taiwanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. A. C. Weber" authorityYear="1902" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Agave" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agave tequilana" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tequilana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Agave tequilana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
F.A.C. Weber (
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Agave" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asparagaceae</taxonomicName>
) as a new species.
</paragraph>
